&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Professionalism:&lt;/strong&gt; Able to work independently, meet deadlines, and respond constructively to

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TOEFL Assessment Consultant&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Study.com is dedicated to making education easily accessible and highly valuable. We are looking for multilingual ESL/TESOL experts to work online and perform quality assurance on TOEFL practice content to help students prepare for one of the world&#39;s most recognized English proficiency exams.&amp;nbsp;This is an online, remote contract role. All work is paid per hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;notion-enable-hover&quot; data-token-index=&quot;0&quot;&gt;As a TOEFL Assessment Consultant, you will:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Review and evaluate user responses to TOEFL/TESOL practice questions using rubrics created by our in-house team&lt;br&gt;- Review and edit written feedback provided to users, ensuring it is accurate, clearly worded and aligned to rubric criteria&lt;br&gt;- Develop deep familiarity with a specific question type (e.g. Write an Email, Virtual Interview, Academic Discussion) and how responses should be structured and scored for that type&lt;br&gt;- Perform peer review by comparing your evaluations against those of fellow contractors and grader-generated scores to ensure consistency and accuracy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in English, ESL, Education or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;TESOL certification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 5 years of experience working with adult ESL learners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 1 year of experience teaching or tutoring TOEFL specifically&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Non-native English speaker with native-level multilingual proficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated familiarity with structured assessment and rubric-based evaluation; teaching specialty (writing, speaking, etc.) is flexible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and ability to apply consistent scoring standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-sufficient and able to work independently as an online contractor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills; this is a collaborative role involving regular interaction with fellow reviewers and the in-house team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with TOEFL 2026 updates and the current exam format&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience evaluating or scoring Academic Discussion, Write an Email, or Virtual Interview question types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background working with adult learners in a university or community college setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reliable Payments: &lt;/strong&gt;You&#39;ll receive payments twice a month and automated invoicing for your work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Remote Work: &lt;/strong&gt;This is a fully online contracted work-from-home opportunity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexibility: &lt;/strong&gt;Work when you want, where you want, and select projects that most interest you.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support: &lt;/strong&gt;Our supportive staff is available answer your questions and help you get up and running.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Contract Process&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete the application and submit with your resume.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Applications are approved and contracts sent on Wednesdays.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Submit the contract within the 5-day signing window.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The following Wednesday, you’ll receive onboarding instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
